        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 6 at 6:57PM CDT by NWS Bismarck ND</headline>
        <description>At 656 PM CDT, a strong thunderstorm was located 9 miles north of
Steele, or 41 miles east of Bismarck, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Steele, Tappen, Dawson, and Horsehead Lake.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, seek shelter inside a building.</instruction>
